ase studies in the United Kingdom and the Netherlands to test political leaders’ and analysts’ claims of successful accommodation and pluralism. Taking Pluralism Seriously provides a clear, fair, and helpful summary of the debate so far in order to understand the promises and pitfalls associated with theories of multiculturalism, interculturalism, federalism, and multinational democracy, investigating the conditions that might make it possible for different national communities to become fully empowered, politically and culturally.Taking Pluralism Seriously invites readers to explore questions of pluralism and accommodation and proposes political reforms to meet the challenges arising from diversity, while considering some of the most pressing concerns complex societies are facing today.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCultural pluralism. 0aMulticulturalism. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Essays.2bisacsh  aCanadian politics.  aConstitutional.  aIndigenous peoples.  aMulticulturalism.  aNetherlands.  aQuebec.  aUnited Kingdom.  afederalism.  ainstitutional asymmetry.  ainterculturalism.  alaicite.  aminority nations.  amultinational democracy.  anationalism.  apolitics.  apublic policy.  asecularization.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311127214608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022z978311127419540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978022801313640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780228013136423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780228013136/original  a978-3-11-127214-6  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-127419-5  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2022b2022  aGBV-deGruyter-alles